THE PURPOSE OF THIS COOPERATIVE AGREEMENT (CA OR AGREEMENT) IS TO SUPPORT THE LIFESAVERS
CONFERENCE, INC. HOST AND COORDINATE A NATIONAL CONFERENCE KNOWN AS THE LIFESAVERS NATIONAL
CONFERENCE ON HIGHWAY SAFETY PRIORITIES. THE ASSISTANCE WILL SUPPORT LIFESAVERS
CONFERENCE, INC. TO TRAIN, EDUCATE AND SHARE INNOVATIVE HIGHWAY SAFETY COUNTERMEASURES AND
SOLUTIONS FOR THE 2023, 2024, 2025, 2026, AND 2027 CONFERENCES. NHTSA WILL PROVIDE
FINANCIAL ASSISTANCE TO SUPPORT THE DISSEMINATION OF TECHNICAL CONTENT AND A FOCUS ON THE
INNOVATIVE RESEARCH AND PROMISING PRACTICES, EXPOSING THE 2000 LIFESAVERS ATTENDEES TO
DIFFERENT WAYS OF THINKING ABOUT APPLYING LESSONS FROM OTHER DISCIPLINES, WHILE THE LIFESAVERS
CONFERENCE, INC. WILL PROVIDE THE MANAGEMENT, DEVELOPMENT AND LOGISTICAL EFFORTS REQUIRED TO
STAGE A NATIONAL CONFERENCE.

THE U.S. DEPARTMENT OF TRANSPORTATION (DOT), NATIONAL HIGHWAY TRAFFIC SAFETY ADMINISTRATION (NHTSA), HEREBY REQUEST AN APPLICATION FOR RENEWAL OF AN EXISTING COOPERATIVE AGREEMENT PROJECT (REFERENCE DTNH2214H00443) WITH THE AMERICAN ASSOCIATION OF MOTOR VEHICLE ADMINISTRATORS (AAMVA), TO ASSIST AAMVA WITH PROVIDING A HELP DESK FOR ITS MEMBER JURISDICTIONS (COVERING ALL 50 STATES AND DC) THAT USE THE PROBLEM DRIVER POINTER SYSTEM (PDPS) SYSTEM.  THE AAMVA HELP DESK SERVES AS A FOCAL POINT FOR THE IDENTIFICATION OF SYSTEM PROBLEMS AND ASSISTS THE JURISDICTIONS, INDIVIDUALLY AND COLLECTIVELY, IN RESOLVING PROBLEMS RELATED TO PDPS OPERATION.  THE AAMVA HELP DESK ALSO PERFORMS TESTING OF APPLICATION CHANGES TO ENSURE SYSTEMS CONTINUE TO PROVIDE THE INFORMATION JURISDICTIONS REQUIRE DAILY.  IN ADDITION, THE AAMVA HELP DESK PROVIDES PDPS RELATED TRAINING AND DOCUMENTATION TO ITS MEMBERS.  THE HELP DESK PERSONNEL WILL BE PRIMARILY AAMVA EMPLOYEES THAT WILL PERFORM ACTIVITIES SUCH AS REPORTING AND MONITORING PROBLEMS, PROVIDING PROCEDURAL INFORMATION, MONITORING SYSTEM AVAILABILITY, PRODUCING DOCUMENTATION, AND TESTING SYSTEM CHANGES.
